unsatisfactoriness gets close to it but it's really the whole gamut of human misery which all of us I'm sure have experienced so it's not only the sort of existential despairs and deep depressions and all that and death it's also the suffering that comes from our indulgence with pleasure the consequences of that the addiction and the grief when you lose somebody lose something

11
00:01:56,367 --> 00:02:05,316
The attachment, the pain, that comes from attachment, which is always hidden, remember, because while you're actually enjoying something, it's heaven, not a problem.

12
