But from the Buddha's point of view it was trying to

30
00:03:52,551 --> 00:04:18,305
see the human being in terms of these five categories we call them heaps aggregates because they're all made up of bits so the first one of course is all to do with the body itself what we experience as sensation and it really is actually only talking about the body that we can sense not the body in itself because the body in itself we know very little of don't we I mean

31
00:04:22,184 --> 00:04:51,415
have you any idea for instance you know what your liver's doing now when you have your biscuits there when you had your biscuits were you directing the amount of enzymes that were going into your stomach to digest it so there's a whole when you look into your body and actually ask yourself you know is this me you find out you don't know much about it directly we know from science you can read about it but in terms of our direct personal experience there's very little

32
00:04:51,749 --> 00:04:54,692
a little that we're actually directly in charge of.

33
00:04:56,394 --> 00:04:58,598
Self-die, multiply, I don't know what they do.

34
00:04:59,399 --> 00:05:01,541
I'm the clue.

35
00:05:01,581 --> 00:05:10,934
I breathe, but it's normally automatic, and something else takes care of this oxygen, carbon dioxide stuff.

36
00:05:10,954 --> 00:05:12,175
I wouldn't know it was there, frankly.

37
00:05:12,615 --> 00:05:13,377
I'm not that I've been told.

38
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:19,545
So, when the Buddha spoke about the body, although that's included,

39
00:05:20,064 --> 00:05:49,920
it's really, really, he's talking about the sentient body, in other words, the body that we can sense through the five senses so it's mainly feeling, mainly feeling there's also sight and hearing direct contact, you see at the very base, remember, right here at the ear drum, all there is, is pressure there's no sound as such so all that's partitioned off, one side, you see

40
00:05:50,947 --> 00:05:53,949
Then there's the next bit which is to do with perceptions.

41
00:05:54,550 --> 00:06:00,156
So I'll put them together, perception and feeling, because in Buddhist psychology it always rides together.

42
00:06:00,377 --> 00:06:03,040
As soon as you have a feeling, the mind, as it were, copies it.

43
00:06:03,781 --> 00:06:04,701
And you have a percept.

44
00:06:05,023 --> 00:06:07,225
It has some sort of mental image to go with it.

45
00:06:08,466 --> 00:06:14,153
