46
00:06:15,014 --> 00:06:17,896
It can be concrete concepts, like Apple.

47
00:06:18,538 --> 00:06:19,519
That can be anything, can't it?

48
00:06:20,107 --> 00:06:47,514
or more abstract, but it all begins with these little percepts and feelings, he splits into those feelings that come into the body through those feelings that come through the body and those feelings that come from the mind in the body, from the heart in the body they include a whole feeling that we have within the body and the thing about Vedana, that's the word he uses

49
00:06:47,848 --> 00:06:55,278
as opposed to the earlier feelings of the body, is that we distinguish them as pleasant or unpleasant.

50
00:06:55,298 --> 00:07:08,216
Up until then, sensations are just neutral, but as soon as we perceive them as pleasant or unpleasant, even neutral, then we move into that area of feeling, feeling perception.

51
00:07:10,559 --> 00:07:12,641
Now the next bit he calls sankāra.

52
00:07:12,773 --> 00:07:42,004
which are those things that we compound, we make up by ourselves and the core ingredient of this is will so now it separates all this to point out that it's at this point that the creation comes in and the will that's creating these Sankara, these habits emotional, mental habits that's our inner atmosphere whatever you're feeling now in your general inner atmosphere whether it's peaceful or un-peaceful whether it's beautiful or un-beautiful

53
00:07:42,473 --> 00:07:46,298
that's been created by acts of will.

54
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:52,187
And what we are experiencing is the conditioning of it.

55
00:07:53,428 --> 00:07:57,093
So the mind is always producing this mental stuff.

56
00:08:00,057 --> 00:08:01,581
And the final one is consciousness.

57
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:11,535
Consciousness here, not to be confused with this pure intelligence of Paññā, the Buddha within.

58
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:17,507
