59
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:20,932
So it's like a television screen.

60
00:08:21,312 --> 00:08:25,379
You've got all this input coming in and it throws it onto a composite picture.

61
00:08:26,961 --> 00:08:31,307
And that basic knowing is what the Buddha is referring to as consciousness.

62
00:08:34,691 --> 00:08:36,813
Now he says that this is the world.

63
00:08:38,971 --> 00:08:41,333
But when he's talking about the world, he's not talking about something objective.

64
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:43,115
He's not talking about something out there.

65
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:50,663
And one of our Western fallacies is to presume that we can know the world as an object.

66
00:08:50,924 --> 00:08:53,927
Something quite objectively outside ourselves.

67
00:08:54,548 --> 00:08:58,052
